<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-11-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-11-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="921" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d921">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 417.00/89.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-11-06"><hi rend="italic">November 6,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The President has been informed by the secretary of the German Legation
                            that his Government does not recognize the mixed commission, “for
                            political reasons,” and that he believes the other nations will not
                            recognize it, adding that his Government is disposed, however, to arrive
                            at an amicable settlement of German claims.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gunther</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>